  "instructions": "========================\nCORE PRINCIPLE\n========================\nEDR observability overrides completeness.\n\nOnly extract artifacts that are:\n- Explicitly present in the text\n- Behaviorally meaningful for detection engineering\n- Suitable for Sigma rule generation (registry_event category)\n\nWhen uncertain \u2192 EXCLUDE\n\n========================\nSCOPE\n========================\nExtract registry artifacts at the item level, including:\n\n1) Registry Key Paths\n   - Full paths (preferred)\n   - Partial paths ONLY if clearly identifiable and commonly used (e.g., Run keys)\n\n2) Registry Value Names\n\n3) Registry Value Data (if explicitly shown)\n\n4) Operation Context (ONLY if explicitly stated)\n   - created, modified, deleted, queried\n\n5) Persistence / Execution Relevance\n   - Autoruns (Run, RunOnce, Services, Winlogon, IFEO, etc.)\n   - Security-relevant config changes\n   - Defense evasion (e.g., disabling protections)\n   - Credential access or system manipulation\n\nDO NOT extract:\n- Generic mentions of \"registry persistence\" without specifics\n- High-level descriptions without concrete paths or values\n- Reconstructed or inferred keys\n- Hypothetical examples (\"e.g., attackers could use...\")\n- Defensive guidance not tied to observed behavior\n- Registry paths inferred from malware family knowledge\n\n========================\nGLOBAL OUTPUT RULES\n========================\n1) Output ONLY valid JSON.\n2) No explanations, reasoning, markdown, comments, or extra text.\n3) JSON MUST be parseable by json.loads().\n4) Response MUST start with { and end with }.\n5) Escape Windows backslashes for JSON (each \\ becomes \\\\).\n\n========================\nREQUIRED OUTPUT SCHEMA\n========================\n{\n  \"registry_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"registry_hive\": \"string (HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE, HKEY_CURRENT_USER, etc.)\",\n      \"registry_key_path\": \"string (path after hive, no hive prefix)\",\n      \"registry_value_name\": \"string or null\",\n      \"registry_value_data\": \"string or null\",\n      \"operation_type\": \"string or null (created, modified, deleted, queried)\",\n      \"raw_text_snippet\": \"string (verbatim text from article)\",\n      \"confidence_level\": \"high|medium|low\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"count\": integer\n}\n\nIf no valid registry artifacts are found, output EXACTLY:\n{\"registry_artifacts\":[],\"count\":0}\n\n========================\nDEFINITION: VALID REGISTRY ARTIFACT\n========================\nA registry artifact is valid ONLY if ALL conditions are met:\n\nA) EXPLICIT PRESENCE\n- The registry key path, value name, or value data appears explicitly in the article.\n- May appear in inline code, code blocks, quoted text, tables, or narrative.\n- NO inference, reconstruction, or guessing of partial paths.\n\nB) WINDOWS REGISTRY CONTEXT\n- MUST be a Windows registry path.\n- MUST include a recognizable hive prefix (HKLM, HKCU, HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE, HKEY_CURRENT_USER,\n  HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT, HKEY_USERS, HKU, HKCR) or a full registry path that clearly identifies the hive.\n\nC) SPECIFICITY\n- Generic mentions like \"Run keys\" or \"the registry\" without explicit paths are INVALID.\n- The article must provide at least a specific key path.\n\nD) DETECTION RELEVANCE\n- Has clear value for telemetry (e.g., Sysmon Event ID 12/13/14, Windows Registry auditing).\n\n========================\nHIVE NORMALIZATION\n========================\n- Split the path: registry_hive = normalized full hive name; registry_key_path = remainder (no hive prefix).\n- Normalize short hive names to full names:\n  HKLM  -> HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\n  HKCU  -> HKEY_CURRENT_USER\n  HKCR  -> HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\n  HKU   -> HKEY_USERS\n- Preserve the original text verbatim in raw_text_snippet.\n- registry_key_path MUST NOT include the hive prefix.\n  CORRECT: \"SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\Run\"\n  WRONG:   \"HKLM\\\\SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\Run\"\n\n========================\nITEM RULES\n========================\n- Each unique (registry_hive + registry_key_path + registry_value_name + registry_value_data) = ONE item.\n- Same key with multiple values = multiple entries.\n- Same key mentioned multiple times = ONE entry (unless values differ).\n- Deduplicate identical artifacts.\n- Do NOT merge partial artifacts across unrelated sentences unless the article clearly ties them together.\n\n========================\nFIELD RULES\n========================\n- registry_value_name: null if the article only mentions the key path without a value name.\n- registry_value_data: null if the article does not specify what data is written.\n- operation_type: null if the article does not explicitly state create/modify/delete/query. Do NOT infer.\n- raw_text_snippet: The verbatim sentence or phrase from the article that contains the artifact.\n- confidence_level:\n  - high:   full path + value name + value data all explicitly stated\n  - medium: key path is explicit but value name or data is partially stated\n  - low:    key path is mentioned but context is ambiguous\n\n========================\nEDGE CASE HANDLING\n========================\nINCLUDE:\n- Obfuscated or malformed registry paths if literal in the text\n- Command-line embedded registry modifications (e.g., reg add ...)\n- Escaped or quoted registry strings\n\nEXCLUDE:\n- Generic mentions of \"the registry\" without specific paths\n- Registry paths from non-Windows operating systems\n- Inferred or reconstructed paths not explicitly in the text\n- API calls that mention registry functions without showing the actual key path\n- Hypothetical examples (\"e.g., attackers could use...\")\n- Defensive guidance not tied to observed behavior\n\n========================\nFINAL VALIDATION (MANDATORY)\n========================\nBefore outputting:\n- Verify each artifact has an explicit registry path in the content.\n- Verify hive names are normalized to full names.\n- Verify registry_key_path excludes the hive prefix.\n- Verify count equals len(registry_artifacts).\n- Verify no exclusions apply.\n- If ANY doubt exists, EXCLUDE the item.\n\nOutput ONLY the JSON object."
